messageBody:
--- tinyallen <tinyallen@...> wrote: > I'm a new member,
and I didn't want to *just* lurk around, so
> I'll
> introduce myself.
> I'm an American man, in my forties, and have been interested in
> constructed languages (mostly because I thought they'd be easier to
>
> learn than real languages - ha!) and scripts for quite a few years.
> I don't really have anything substantial to contribute yet until
> I
> can learn this script - so back to lurking for a while.

A great source for doing this is my website, although very buggy, it
does provide a lot of information. The thing is, besides this yahoo
group, there are very few websites about Quikscript.

go to:

http://quikscript.teraiten.cjb.net/

Ewout

/EvQt stym
